<br>
In regards to investigating every case, thats a very ambiguous statement Scirocco.  That can mean just asking the customer a few questions and then saying we've investigated and your banned.  To be honest i dont know how time conusming it is from their standpoint to fully investigate every account hacking or where a person claims they were hacked.  Just about everybody that gets their account hacked will claim they were legitemately hacked regardless of them allowing others to use their account, similar to the incident mentioned with Ungaba or whatever her/his name was.  People that give out their PW's to others dont think those 'friends' will hack their account, so they'll assume its a real hacker.  Then Verant has to investigate due to public outcry with whatever resources they have, and then later determine it was in fact the customers fault for being stupid.  Thats wasted time and resources.  But your right, there probably are legitemate account hackings with no fault on the customers side and those shouldnt be overlooked.  <br>
To summarize the whole point of my post, people WANT to blame Verant for everything bad in EQ, when in fact the customers should bear alot of blame.  Of course its unfair to some customers, cuz not ALL customers are as stupid as others.  But we are categorized as a whole in regards to Verants policies.<br>
<br>
